      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think this was done to avoid extra refs/derefs. I one says sk_ref_sp(this) one gets a sk_sp\u003cLogFontTypeface const\u003e since this is const here. This is a different type from sk_sp\u003cLogFontTypeface\u003e which the SkScalerContext_GDI takes, so that copy will be made incrementing the ref count again. This secondary ref gets moved to the SkScalerContext_GDI constructor parameter, but the first temporary still exists and will need to be unrefed at the \u0027;\u0027 at the end of this expression.\n\nSo the cast avoids an extra ref/unref pair.",
